President Biden has authorized increased disaster assistance for the state of New Mexico, specifically for debris removal and emergency protective measures due to wildfires, winds, flooding, mudflows, and debris flows that occurred between April 5 and July 23, 2022. The President previously declared federal funds for debris removal and emergency measures at 100% of eligible costs for a 90-day period starting from May 4, 2022. Now, this funding has been extended for an additional 90-day period from August 3, 2022, to November 1, 2022, specifically for Mora and San Miguel Counties. Media seeking further information can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.